  "prompt": "What is a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Power County ID?",
  "response": "As of my last update, there are several options for inpatient drug and alcohol rehab centers that serve individuals in Power County, Idaho. However, specific recommendations might change over time, so it's important to verify the current status and details of the facilities. Here are some general options you can consider:\n\n1. **Portneuf Valley Family Center Counseling** in Pocatello, ID - They offer a range of treatment services, although their inpatient options should be verified directly.\n\n2. **Bannock House** in Pocatello, ID - This facility offers residential treatment and can be a good option for those needing structured inpatient care.\n\n3. **Moonlight Mountain Recovery** in Pocatello, ID - They provide comprehensive addiction treatment programs, including inpatient care, and are relatively close to Power County.\n\n4. **Raise the Bottom Training and Counseling Services** in various locations, though primarily in Boise, ID - They offer a range of addiction treatment services, including residential programs.\n\nTo find the best fit for your needs, consider contacting these centers to inquire about specific services, treatment approaches, and availability. It may also be advisable to speak with a healthcare provider or counselor who can offer tailored recommendations based on individual circumstances. Additionally, checking online reviews and reaching out to local health departments can provide more current information on the best options available.",
